Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting significant renal impairment and possible diabetic or metabolic derangement, despite a low HbA1c. Urine is dilute, cloudy, brown, and ammoniacal, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Further evaluation of renal function, diabetes status, and possible acute or chronic kidney disease is recommended.
